### Step 1 — Prepare and Validate

One-line goal. Precede each command block with a single sentence saying what it is for.

Syntax-check and confirm the environment resolves:

```bash
cd "$FRACTOGENESIS_HOME"
bash -n bin/{{PRIMARY_SCRIPT}}
```

Preview without changing anything, when the script supports it:

```bash
./bin/{{PRIMARY_SCRIPT}} {{DRY_RUN_FLAG}}
```

> [!note]
> {{an easily-missed fact about this step}}.

### Step 2 — Execute the Primary Action

Run the primary script with any required arguments:

```bash
./bin/{{PRIMARY_SCRIPT}} [--artifact-root "$REIMAGE_ARTIFACT_ROOT"]
```

What it writes and where (refer to the names defined in Artifact and Script Locations, do not redraw the tree):

```text
$REIMAGE_ARTIFACT_ROOT/{{ARTIFACT_PATHS}}
```

### Step 3 — Verify Outputs

Confirm success before moving on:

```bash
find "$REIMAGE_ARTIFACT_ROOT/{{ARTIFACT_PATHS}}" -maxdepth 2 -type f | sort | head
```

